Restored full text of the inscription:

 1.wddʾl | rymn | bn | ʾbkrb | bn | ṣbḥrm | ḏ-ḫll
 2.bʿṯtr | bn | wddʾl | bn | ṣbḥrm | ḏ-ḫll | ywm | ršw | ʿṯtr |
 3.w-fdy-hw | bn | kl | ʾbyt-hw | w-sqy | ʿṯtr | ḫrf | w-dṯʾ | b-ršwt-hw |
 4.ln | yḥwr | ʿd(y) | nšqm |
 5.ʿmkrb | bn | wddʾl | bn | ṣbḥrm | ḏ-ḫll |
 6.ywm | ršw | ʿṯtr | w-fdy-hw | bn | kl | ʾby=
 7.t-hw | w-sqy | ʿṯtr | sbʾ | w-gw[m]
 8.ḫrf | w-dṯʾ</tei:ab>
            </div>
            <div xml:lang="en" type="translation">
                <tei:ab xmlns:tei="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="adlib-orig">Text preserved in this squeeze:

4.since he settled in
5.ʿAmmīkarib bin Wa[...]
6.[whe]n he served as priest of ʿAth[tar ... ... ...] his
7.[...]. And ʿAth[tar] provided irrigation
8.during the autumn and spring.


Restored full text of the inscription:

1.[Wadadʾīl Raymān bin ʾAbīkarib, of the lineage of Ṣabaḥrām Dhū-Khalīl.]
2.[Biʿathtar bin Wadadʾīl, of the lineage of Ṣabaḥrām Dhū-Khalīl, (had this inscription carved) when he served as priest of (the god) ʿAthtar,]
3.[and he (i.e. ʿAthtar) absolved him of his duties with respect to all of his temples. And ʿAthtar provided irrigation during the autumn and spring, during his priesthood,]
4.since he settled in (the town of) [Nashqum.]
5.ʿAmmīkarib bin Wa[dadʾīl, of the lineage of Ṣabaḥrām Dhū-Khalīl, (had this inscription carved)]
6.[whe]n he served as priest of ʿAt[htar. And he (i.e. ʿAthtar) absolved him of his duties with respect to all of] his
7.[templ]es. And ʿAth[tar] provided irrigation [for Sabaʾ and the community]
8.during the autumn and spring.</tei:ab>
            </div>
